<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,511,752]" box="[199,1250,583,607]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
Distribution in 
<collectingCountry box="[370,442,583,607]" name="Brazil" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Brazil</collectingCountry>
: Southeast and South regions (
<collectingRegion box="[786,832,583,607]" country="Brazil" name="MG" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">MG</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[843,880,584,607]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">PR</collectingRegion>
, SC) (
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser &amp; Polhemus" box="[949,1237,583,607]" firstAuthor="Nieser" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="53 - 76" refId="ref41419" refString="Nieser, N. &amp; Polhemus, D. A. (1999) Four new species of Rhagovelia (Heteroptera: Veliidae) from Minas Gerais (Brazil), with a key to the regional species of the angustipes complex. Aquatic Insects, 21, 53 - 76." type="journal article" year="1999">Nieser &amp; Polhemus 1999</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,511,752]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
Comments: This species was recorded from 
<collectingRegion box="[723,839,620,644]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[903,1074,620,644]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
states by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ribeiro, J. R. I. &amp; Estevez, A. L." firstAuthor="Moreira" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="207 - 215" refId="ref42676" refString="Ribeiro, J. R. I. &amp; Estevez, A. L. (2009) The small species of Belostoma Latreille (Heteroptera, Belostomatidae). III. A revision of the oxyurum group, with a new species from Brazil and description of the male of B. noualhieri Montandon. Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 53, 207 - 215." type="journal article" year="2009">Moreira and Ribeiro (2009)</bibRefCitation>
. A careful examination of the specimens cited in that study, including male parameres, revealed that specimens from 
<collectingRegion box="[277,388,692,716]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
were actually representatives of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bacon" authorityYear="1956" box="[756,879,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Rhagovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis box="[756,879,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">R. modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and that from 
<collectingRegion box="[1049,1211,692,716]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Drake &amp; Harris" authorityYear="1933" box="[1222,1379,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Rhagovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hambletoni">
<emphasis box="[1222,1379,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">R. hambletoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The occurrence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Drake" authorityYear="1958" box="[311,427,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Rhagovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabrina">
<emphasis box="[311,427,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">R. sabrina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in both states must be therefore unconsidered.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
